The article highlights President Donald J. Trump's efforts to implement the most extensive regulatory reform in American history. The aim of this reform is to eliminate unnecessary and expensive regulations that negatively impact American businesses and families. President Trump is focused on reducing costs for consumers and providing support to low-income Americans who are disproportionately affected by overregulation. The administration's deregulatory initiatives are ultimately intended to boost the economy by putting more money in the pockets of Americans and fostering business growth.